The paper deals with power control problems in network communication, which is a topic covered by several sub-categories in computer science. The use of gradient-based iterations and saddle point methods suggests that the paper may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The focus on constrained convex optimization problems and the use of running averages suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the application of the method to spectrum sharing problems suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.MA (Multiagent Systems).
